# Take-home submission (TASK.md)

Follow these requirements for all code and documentation work in this repository.

## Allowed tools

Search engines and AI assistants are **encouraged**. Record every substantive tool in `docs/TOOL.md` (or the project’s designated tool list): for each entry, state **what problem it solved** and **usage scenario or key steps**. Include IDE, AI tools, search, and notable npm dependencies.

## Code

- Write **code comments in English**.
- Deliver a **complete, working** solution; **`npm run dev` must start successfully**.
- Prefer aligning implementation with **`README.md` challenge goals** (UI behavior, bugs, persistence, TypeScript, responsive & accessible UI).

## Documentation (English)

- Maintain **`REFLECTION.md`**: describe **which bugs were fixed** (concrete) and **how performance was optimized** (methods and tradeoffs).
- Do not invent submission artifacts; update them as work completes.

## AI usage record

- Preserve **full, unedited** transcripts of AI-assisted work (no summarizing in place of the original).
- Store them as **`docs/AI_LOG.md`** and/or exported text/screenshots, per task instructions.

## Submission expectations (human workflow)

- **Fork** the upstream repo to your own GitHub; keep a **public, accessible** repository URL for hand-in.
- Package code and docs as required by the employer; ensure the repo reflects the final state.
